Input minigene reporters (in two technical replicates) and output spliced species for each of the four transfection were sequenced on an Illumina HiSeq 3000 (2 × 150). Reads from input and output sequencing were aligned to minigene reporter sequences using the STAR aligner60 (version 2.5.1b). For input alignment, split reads were not allowed, whereas for output alignment, split reads were allowed. Uniquely mapped reads with up to ten mismatches were tabulated for each input and output sequencing library, and were shown to be highly correlated across input and output replicates (Supplementary Fig. 5). The M/W splice ratio for each de novo variant was calculated as \documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
